Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! It’s nice to see you again.
It’ll be nice to have more farmers here.//Being able to get local produce will be a game changer.
I went for a run in the forest this morning and got back before <NPCName>Valentina</> had to leave for school.//It’s a great way to start the day.
Hmm? Oh sure. Sort of like a wake-up call.
It’s sad to think about, but…//If I don’t take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school now, when else would I get to do it?
Soon she’ll be all grown up, then off to university…//<portrait=annoyed>Time really does fly, <PlayerName>$player</>.
My sis, <NPCName>Alice</>, is so soft-spoken. I can barely hear what she’s saying half the time.
That girl needs to turn it up a notch.//Speak up more!
<NPCName>Alice</> and I are twins, correct… But no, I can’t read her mind.
She can’t feel it when I get pinched, either.//And no, we don’t do everything together.
I try to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school every morning.//Then I can pick up stuff for the inn on the way home.
It’s sad to think about, but…//If I don’t take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school now, when else would I get to do it?
Soon she’ll be all grown up, then off to university…//<portrait=annoyed>Time really does fly, <PlayerName>$player</>.
It’s sad to think about, but…//If I don’t take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school now, when else would I get to do it?
Soon she’ll be all grown up, then off to university…//<portrait=annoyed>Time really does fly, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Hmm? Oh sure. Sort of like a wake-up call.
I try to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school every morning.//Then I pick up some stuff for the inn on the way home.
I let <NPCName>Alice</> pick our wine selection.//I don’t care about alcohol.
Besides, we get our wine from Hillside Vineyard…//Their business seems to be doing well, so whatever they’re making must be good.
My sister may look small, but gosh, can she eat!//<portrait=happy>Especially when she makes minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=normal>A healthy appetite is good!
It’s one of her favorite dishes, by the way.//That and green smoothies… Same as me!
My sis, <NPCName>Alice</>, is so soft-spoken. I can barely hear what she’s saying half the time.
That girl needs to turn it up a notch.//Speak up more.

Besides, we get our wine from Hillside Vineyard…//Their business seems to be doing well, so whatever they’re making must be good.

That’s one of her favorite dishes, by the way.//That and green smoothies… Same as me!
I let <NPCName>Alice</> pick our wine selection.//I don’t care about alcohol.
Besides, we get our wine from Hillside Vineyard…//Their business seems to be doing well, so whatever they’re making must be good.
<NPCName>Alice</> and I are twins, correct… But no, I can’t read her mind.
She can’t feel it when I get pinched, either.//And no, we don’t do everything together.
Have you ever tried making eggplant lasagna? It’s delicious, and it’s really easy to make.//But you do need a ceramic bowl.
Yeah, I make it all the time.//I know the recipe by heart.
Have you ever tried making eggplant lasagna? It’s delicious, and it’s really easy to make.//But you do need a ceramic bowl.
Yeah, I make it all the time.//I know the recipe by heart.
The inn does okay, but it isn’t packed…//Well, not as packed as I’d like it to be!//<portrait=happy>But we do have a few regulars.
Oh, that’s right! You’re probably friends with them, huh?//<NPCName>Eva</> and <NPCName>Macy</>?
It’s Friday again. No school for the kids tomorrow.
I need to make sure <NPCName>Valentina</> does her weekend reading.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes she gets carried away and forgets about it.
Does the air smell musty to you?//I’m worried the inn might have mold.
We get a lot of tourists who come here just to go diving.
Some only visit Coral Island for the festivals.//<portrait=normal>We’re kind of famous, if you think about it.
Have you ever tried making eggplant lasagna? It’s delicious, and it’s really easy to make.//But you do need a ceramic bowl.
I make it often here.
I put out my old sewing machine for the community to use.//It’s never too late to learn a new skill.
We get a lot of tourists who come here just to dive.
There are also people who only visit Coral Island for the festivals.
It’s Sunday again. The kids are back to school tomorrow.
I need to make sure <NPCName>Valentina</> does her weekend reading.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes she gets carried away and forgets about it.
The inn does okay, but it isn’t crowded…//Well, not as crowded as I’d like it to be!//<portrait=happy>But we do have a few regulars.
Oh, that’s right! You’re probably friends with them, huh?//<NPCName>Eva</> and <NPCName>Macy</>?
Let me tell you something about my sister. <NPCName>Alice</> took a neuroscience class on zombies, and they did a behavioral study to compare zombie brains to human brains.
Of course not. Zombies aren’t real. Don’t be silly!
And get this, yeah? <NPCName>Alice</> also took an astrobiology class on the search for extraterrestrial life. I don’t know what she was thinking…
Don’t know if you know this. But I used to be fun, <PlayerName>$player</>. Now I get excited about a trip to the grocery store.
Gotta love the new me, I guess.
What do you have on the agenda for the week?
I don’t talk about it a lot, but having a child really did something to my life. It changed me…
Oh, in a good way, of course. Being a parent gives me a whole new sense of purpose.
I never cared about my diet or lifestyle until I had <NPCName>Valentina</>. Then I became a label-reading momster. Ha!
Not even going to deny it. It’s who I am now.
My ex’s cousin <NPCName>Rafael</> helps out with odd jobs around the inn when he comes to visit <NPCName>Valentina</> on Sundays.
You know him, don’t you? Yeah, he’s pretty helpful.
My ex’s cousin <NPCName>Rafael</> helps out with odd jobs around the inn when he comes to visit <NPCName>Valentina</> on Sundays.
You know him, don’t you? Yeah, he’s pretty helpful.
I never used to care about my diet or lifestyle until I had <NPCName>Valentina</>. Then I became a label-reading momster. Ha!
Not even going to deny it. It’s who I am now.
Don’t know if you do know this, but… I used to be fun, <PlayerName>$player</>. Now I get excited for a trip to the grocery store.
Gotta love the new me, I guess.
I never cared about my diet or lifestyle until I had <NPCName>Valentina</>. Then I became a label-reading momster. Ha!
Not even going to deny it. It’s who I am now.
Don’t know if you do know this, but… I used to be fun, <PlayerName>$player</>. Now I get excited for a trip to the grocery store.
Gotta love the new me, I guess.
Let me tell you something about my sister. <NPCName>Alice</> took a neuroscience class on zombies, and they did a behavioral study to compare zombie brains to human brains.
Of course not. Zombies aren’t real. Don’t be silly!
And get this, yeah? <NPCName>Alice</> also took an astrobiology class on the search for extraterrestrial life. I don’t know what she was thinking…
A lot of cleaning up to do today…
Well, that’s what weekends are for. So I might as well get to work.
I had <NPCName>Valentina</> when I was pretty young. But I want to be there for her for as long as possible.
That’s why I’m keeping a close eye on what I eat. No more junk food, thanks!
I’m pretty physically active, but I just can’t get into the activities my ex loves.
Rock climbing? Diving?//None of those.
Are you ready for Spring cleaning, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I am. I’ve prepared for this all year.
Oh, aren’t you glad Winter is over? I certainly am. Besides the snow, the cold was unbearable.
The inn is so big… It’s not easy to clean it alone.//I don’t mind, though. I even make my own cleaning solution.
*singing* Clean, clean, clean~
I’m sure glad I don’t have to run in the cold anymore!//The great thing about running is after a while, you warm up and you don’t feel the cold anymore. But starting out is hard.
I love running in Spring.//<portrait=normal>It’s so nice to hear all the animals again and see all the plants blooming.//<portrait=happy>It gives me more energy to run!
Now that Winter is over, I need to wash all the blankets and put them in storage.
<NPCName>Valentina’s</> birthday is coming up soon. It’s on the 3rd of Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Should I have a big birthday party at the inn, or should we just go for a picnic at the beach?
I’ve cleaned everything on my list. Phew, finished right on schedule!
<NPCName>Valentina</> gets really active in Summer. I think she’s excited to go out and play with her dad.
It gets pretty hot and humid living by the beach… I can’t wear too many layers.
It’s nice to see people getting together and cleaning up the beach.//One of my favorite things about Summer.
I made some homemade bug repellent, but it doesn’t seem to work.//Or maybe the Summer bugs are just super strength…
I put out my homemade bug repellent in the lobby. It’s free for everybody to use… And guests can take a mini bottle with them if they want.
Lemongrass is the main ingredient in my bug repellent… It smells really strong.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t hate it… It’s just… No point using perfume, you know? It would just be overpowered.
Oh, I better make some minced jackfruit pies for dinner with some fresh jackfruit. It’s in season now!//Sounds so yum!
I’m a little sad Spring is over, but Summer isn’t so bad.
I wonder if it’d be worth it to turn on the sprinklers so the grass stays green… Or is that just a waste of water?
Some of the guests complained about the yellow grass… No, no, not recently. It was a few years ago.//I told them it’s just the way the grass is here, but they wouldn’t accept it.
We’re bracing ourselves for the oncoming Winter. You should, too.//Heater, blankets… What else do I need?
Fall is really nice, isn’t it? Very beautiful.
I like running in Fall. It’s cool enough that I don’t feel overheated but not too cold that I feel like I’m freezing my toes off.

We usually get more guests the closer we get to the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=concerned>Some of them are up from Beluga Bay for the harvest display, and the rest are just tourists who are curious about the festival.

I have to make sure the heaters are working properly before Winter starts… <Italic>Oh!</> And see that we have enough blankets for everyone.//<portrait=annoyed>I asked <NPCName>Alice</> to take care of the blankets a few years ago, but she missed some of the rooms, so I’m taking care of them now.

I have to get the blanket boxes from storage.//I’m gonna ask <NPCName>Rafael</> to do it next weekend… And I have to check the battery in the carbon monoxide detector.//I do it every year at the very least!
You can just run longer in cooler weather. You don’t get out of breath as easily.//Me, I mean…not you.
Oh, here we go. It’s Winter again…
Good news! We have enough blankets for the guests…I think.//Let’s hope!
I know it’s my birthday month, but honestly, I don’t really care about birthdays… The best thing about mine is <NPCName>Alice</>.
<NPCName>Valentina</> can be <Italic>very</> excessive when it comes to accessorizing her snowmen. She sneaks and takes my robe, my hat…//Some of the things she takes are Wabanana, you know…
Ugh, I don’t want to give up my morning runs, but I’m seriously considering it.//<portrait=concerned>It’s so cold!
Our birthday is coming soon. What should I do for <NPCName>Alice</>? Hmm…
I can’t believe I have a twin… It always blows my mind when our birthday is coming up.
I’m looking forward to Spring.//Making my cleaning solution tonight… Getting ready for Spring cleaning. Woo-hoo!
Phew! Quite a party last night, yeah?
I don’t think I got enough sleep… I still feel very tired.
It’s <NpcName>Joko’s</> birthday tomorrow… Hmm…//<portrait=normal>Do you think I should get him some pineapples? Or a jar of yogurt?
Yeah, I think he would appreciate it.
Okay. It’s a healthy snack.

Special.SourceString: Eww, not pineapples. A jar of yogurt, of course.

Text.SourceString: I expected to see more rain than this.
You know, I have to say… Quite a name you’ve got, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Is there a meaning behind it?
My parents never explained why they named me <NPCName>Suki</> and my sister <NPCName>Alice</>…
I ate so much yesterday at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I think I’m still full today. *laughs*
The beach cleanup is an awesome thing, but we also need to remember to use less plastic and recycle.
I get fresh flowers for the inn from <NPCName>Ben</>.//He gives us a discount for buying in bulk.
We get things from <NPCName>Sam’s</> store too, of course…//<portrait=happy>Um… You know, bread and things like that.
I’m only here to pick up some irises for the inn from <NPCName>Ben</>.
I’m only here to pick up some irises for the inn from <NPCName>Ben</>.
The sun sure is strong today… Be sure to stay hydrated, okay?
A lot of people are very dedicated to this island.//It was great to see all of us together yesterday.
It’s starting to get chilly at night.
Make sure to bring your best produce to the Harvest Festival on the 15th.
I thought it started to snow last night, but no. *sighs*
I was so excited.
What should I cook for tomorrow? If I can’t settle on something, I’m going to skip it and heat up some leftovers.
No big deal…
<NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I suppose you already knew that. I remember playing around town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Building rows of snowmen.
Great memories all around.
Animals can have a positive effect on our mental health. Did you know that? I’ve tried having pets, but they don’t seem to like the inn very much.
Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> dinner party on the 28th? I don’t know if I should bring wine or something.
I’m not too worried about <NPCName>Valentina</>.//She knows to be careful when the ground is slippery.
Her father takes her climbing all the time, and she’s good at it.
<NPCName>Valentina</> always gives me a hard time at bedtime…//Whenever I complain to her father about it, he just says she doesn’t do it at his place.

Gah… Of course she doesn’t do it with him. I don’t even want to know what time he puts her to bed.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m sure that’s why she doesn’t give him trouble.//<portrait=concerned>Midnight bedtime, for crying out loud!
<NPCName>Valentina</> always gives me a hard time at bedtime…//Whenever I complain to her father about it, he just says she doesn’t do it at his place.

Gah… Of course she doesn’t do it with him. I don’t even want to know what time he puts her to bed.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m sure that’s why <NPCName>Valentina</> doesn’t give him trouble.//<portrait=concerned>Midnight bedtime, for crying out loud!
It gets a bit cold in here, yeah?
I wish the school would give the kids the day off when it’s stormy like this.
Careful on your way home, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Take Garden Lane tonight, will you?//It might be safer than going through the lookout.
Well, I just thought it might be more slippery.
<NPCName>Valentina</> always gives me a hard time at bedtime…//Whenever I complain to her father about it, he just says she doesn’t do it at his place.

Gah… Of course she doesn’t do it with him. I don’t even want to know what time he puts her to bed.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m sure that’s why <NPCName>Valentina</> doesn’t give him trouble.//<portrait=concerned>Midnight bedtime, for crying out loud!
We need to find out how to crank up the heat in here.
The snow is piling up outside.
Winter isn’t my favorite season, but days like these may make me reconsider.
<NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I guess you already knew that. I remember playing around the town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age… Building rows of snowmen.
Great memories all around.
*singing* Dum dum dum…~ <Italic>Dum!</>~
[<NPCName>Suki</> is singing. She doesn’t sound bad.]
Oh, here, let me show you how to make a green smoothie.//It’s delicious, and it’s a power drink too.
A bit stuffy in here. We need to open more windows…
You should take a break from farm life and stay here for a weekend or something.
You can just relax and read a book in your room with the windows open.//<portrait=happy>Fall asleep to the calming sound of the waves…
We’ll give you the local discount! Heh heh.
We have plenty of books in our library.//If you don’t mind well-read books, please help yourself.
Guests are welcome to take a book to read in exchange for one they’re finished with.
It’s a “take a book, leave a book” type system…//But if someone doesn’t have a book to donate, it’s okay. They don’t have to leave anything.
You should check out the pier. There are usually tons of seals out at this time.
<NPCName>Valentina</> needs to clean up that room of hers, or she’s not playing at the beach tomorrow.
That girl… When it’s time to surf or play with her friends, then she’s out the door in seconds.//But when it comes to cleaning up her room… Oh gosh!
What are you doing here so early in the morning?
Going fishing, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I should pick up some books and brochures for the inn while I’m here.
But I haven’t returned the books we borrowed last week.//<portrait=annoyed>I wonder if <NPCName>Millie</> will make a big deal out of it.
I’m here to pick up some fresh fruit and veggies for dinner. You?
Flowers are a little expensive here. So I usually get them from <NPCName>Ben</> instead.//Besides, I sometimes buy out-of-season flowers that <NPCName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.
Sorry, <NPCName>Sam</>!
I’m feeling good today. I’m bringing my A game. *laughs*
Come here to play?
I think the mini golf course Pufferfish built is a great addition to our town.
I feel bad for saying it, but I like mini golf.//It does feel like a betrayal to be enjoying it, though… I don’t know what to tell ya.
She and I grew up together here…//<portrait=happy>Oh! <NPCName>Nina</>… I was talking about <NPCName>Nina</>.
Thank you for this! It will make a very fresh green smoothie. I’ll send you the recipe tomorrow.
So, how much do I owe you?
<NPCName>Valentina</> keeps asking if she can go to the forest by herself.//<portrait=annoyed>I just don’t think it’s safe.

I’m not worried about people, really… You never know what else lives there.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t actually believe it… But nothing’s wrong with being careful, I think.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… <NPCName>Alice</>has gotten her outrageous theories into my head.
<Italic>Finding Love from Within</> is my absolute favorite book.//It gives you insights into a lot of things. I find myself always moving forward.
Hmm… That’s true, but I like Rachel Abram’s version much better.//I read both hers and Tyna Smith’s <Italic> Finding Love from Within</>. They’re entirely different books.

<NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> come to the inn a lot.//<portrait=happy>They’re great uncles to Valentina. Their whole family is very affectionate… Lovey-dovey, you know?//<portrait=normal>I’m grateful <NPCName>Valentina</> was born into their family.
<NPCName>Rafael</> or <NPCName>Pablo</>? What?! Neither of them is my ex.//<portrait=happy>My ex-husband is <NPCName>Antonio</>… One of their cousins.
Oh my! <PlayerName>$player</>, what day is it?//<portrait=normal>Tuesday? Thank goodness. I thought I missed a day in my cardio routine.//It’s okay. I’m okay!

According to this book I’m reading, we should all be more grateful. It’s supposed to lead to a 15 percent increase in happiness within two weeks.//<portrait=happy>I’m giving it a try. I mean, why not?
I’ve been keeping a gratitude journal for a week.//In just seven more days, I’ll be a new, happier me!
You meet a lot of people working at an inn.//Traveling does that too.

The inn is a great place to live.//It may not be a conventional place to grow up, under the same roof as strangers and all. But <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up there, and we had fun.//<portrait=happy>I think <NPCName>Valentina</> will do just fine.
I like to change up my exercise routine each week so I don’t get bored.
<NPCName>Valentina</> is the same way. She gets bored quickly.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, her dad keeps her active with things like volleyball and rock climbing.
If you ever need a place to stay, you’re welcome at the inn.
I don’t know why you’d need it since you have a house of your own, but the offer stands.
Have you ever gone for a sunrise jog on the beach?//It clears your head.
I don’t want my head to be too clear, though. There are a lot of things I need to remember.
I run in the forest on Monday mornings… If the weather permits, that is.//<portrait=happy>I’ll hit the woodland tomorrow morning. I usually run back to the inn after taking <NPCName>Val</> to school.
Yep, correct! <NPCName>Val</> is <NPCName>Valentina</>.
I run to the forest on Monday mornings… If the weather permits, that is.//<portrait=happy>I’ll hit the woodland tomorrow morning. I usually run back to the inn after taking <NPCName>Val</> to school.
Yep, correct! <NPCName>Val</> is <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Deep breath in, deep breath out. Peace from within.
Okay, I’m good now. Do you need something, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Don’t tell anyone, but I may have eaten one strawberry too many yesterday.//They’re so sweet! I’m not usually a big fan of strawberries, but I could eat some more, to be honest.
Wait, were they from your farm?//<portrait=normal>I got them from Sam’s.

I often see you walking past the inn. Been going to the diving spot, huh?//<portrait=happy>Good for you, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m glad for people like you… People who care not only about themselves but also about our environment.
Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re very cool!
I’m glad <NPCName>Valentina</> is close with <NPCName>Antonio’s</> family.//With her school as small as it is, I have to make sure she gets the social interaction she needs.
I hope the more people <NPCName>Valentina</> is exposed to, the more she’ll learn about diversity, and the better her social skills will be.
The inn is always open, seven days a week.//We have to be there for the weekenders.
There’s always so much cleaning to do at the inn.//I don’t mind, though. It keeps me moving.
I wish <NPCName>Alice</> would make more friends.//Spend less time reading up on those silly things she’s so interested in and actually live her life.

Sorry, that was rude. Those things aren’t silly.//It’s just…<NPCName>Alice</> is too focused on them, and she doesn’t have any friends.//<portrait=concerned>Well, yeah. Valid point. <NPCName>Noah</> is her friend… But that’s the problem, isn’t it? <NPCName>Noah’s</> her <Italic>only</> friend.
My day’s been fantastic so far! Thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Valentina</> just got her report card today. All As, as usual.
Me? Nope. My grades were so-so. She must take after <NPCName>Antonio</>.//<portrait=happy>I was too busy having fun to focus on school.
Someone made a huge mess in one of the rooms at the inn a few days ago.//<portrait=concerned>It took me the whole day to clean up.
<NPCName>Antonio</> and I fought last night. That rarely happens, so it bothers me when it does.//<portrait=concerned>He said I’m too naggy about <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Maybe <NPCName>Antonio</> has a point… But I just want the best for her.
I wonder what <NPCName>Valentina</> will be when she grows up.//<portrait=normal>Whatever it is, I hope she finds her passion. Her dad and I will be right there, supporting her.
The inn is ours…yeah. My parents used to run it before <NPCName>Alice</> and I took over.
You look surprised! Ha ha! Interesting reaction.
Hmm… I can’t remember if I told <NPCName>Alice</> to clean out the inn’s reception desk or not.
I hope she does it regardless. It could use some tidying up.
Do you know of any good places to get exercise gear?//Wabanana is great, but I can try other brands if you have any suggestions.
Brooke, <NPCName>Charles’s</> ex, used to go shopping with me at Wabanana.
It’s Friday! Got anything fun planned for the weekend?//<portrait=normal>I think I’m going to take it easy.
Even though <NPCName>Antonio</> and I got divorced, I’m happy for the time we had together.//I have <NPCName>Valentina</> because of him, after all, and he’s taught me a lot about myself.
Every once in a while, I think about <NPCName>Antonio’s</> parents. His mom made killer burritos.//<portrait=happy>I wonder how they’re doing.
I stepped on a rusty can during my jog this morning! Thank goodness I had my thick shoes on.
I need to tell <NPCName>Valentina</> not to go barefoot on the beach.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry.
It’s so nice having <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> around on Sundays.//They can keep an eye on <NPCName>Valentina</> while I run errands.
I had a huge to-do list I wanted to get through yesterday, but I wasn’t able to finish everything.//Normally I’d be upset about it, but I feel…okay?
I’ll just roll everything over to today. It’s not a big deal.//Wow, that feels weird to say…but in a good way.
Ah, it’s my favorite time of year! Know why? It’s time for Spring cleaning!//<portrait=happy>Out with the old, in with the new!
Spring is the perfect time to start new habits.//Everyone’s shaking off the Winter cold and getting outside again.
What sort of flowers should I plant around the inn this year?//I’ll have to check my plant notebook for ideas.
I’ll plant anything but violets.//<portrait=annoyed>I just hate the way they smell.
Summer is a good time to burn away bad vibes.//Just lie back on the beach and let the sun do its thing.//Don’t forget sunscreen, though!
I need to keep an eye on how much candy <NPCName>Valentina</> eats.//She’ll make herself sick otherwise.
I can’t believe it’s time for <NPCName>Valentina</> to start another year of school. She’s growing up way too fast.
<NPCName>Antonio</> and I used to spend Fall going to concerts and music festivals. I can’t really see myself doing that anymore.
There’s so much fresh food to cook with in Fall. It makes planning <NPCName>Valentina’s</> meals much easier.
She <Italic>loves</> red curry but can’t eat mushrooms.//Poor thing.
Have you made your plans for Winter yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Now’s the time to get started.
We don’t get many customers at the inn in Winter.//I think people prefer to stay in their own houses during the cold months.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know. What do you think?
I grew up here, and I’m still having a hard time adjusting to this weather.
